    • Method Detail

      • dispatchSaveInstanceState

        public void dispatchSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle outState)

        Called to save state of this adapter module instance. If the given outState is invalid, there will be created a new bundle and onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) will be invoked immediately.

        Parameters:
        outState - Outgoing state in which should this adapter module instance save its state.
        See Also:
        onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle)

      • dispatchRestoreInstanceState

        public void dispatchRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle savedState)

        Called to restore state of this adapter module instance. If the given savedState is valid, onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) will be invoked immediately.

        Parameters:
        savedState - Should be the bundle with saved state in onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle).
        See Also:
        onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle)

      • dispatchAttachToAdapter

        public final void dispatchAttachToAdapter(Adapter adapter)

        Called to attach this adapter module to the given adapter.

        Parameters:
        adapter - The adapter to which will be this adapter module attached.

      • isAdapterNotificationEnabled

        public boolean isAdapterNotificationEnabled()

        Returns flag indicating whether the adapter to which is this module attached should be notified in case, that the data set of this adapter module was changed.

        Returns:
        True in case, that adapter notification is enabled, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        enableAdapterNotification(boolean)

      • enableAdapterNotification

        public void enableAdapterNotification(boolean enable)

        Sets flag indicating whether the adapter to which is this module attached should be notified in case, that the data set of this adapter module was changed.

        Parameters:
        enable - True to enable, false to disable.
        See Also:
        isAdapterNotificationEnabled()

      • onSaveInstanceState

        protected void onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle outState)

        Invoked to save state of this adapter module instance. This is invoked whenever dispatchSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) is called.

        Parameters:
        outState - Outgoing state. Always valid bundle.
        See Also:
        onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle)

      • onRestoreInstanceState

        protected void onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle savedState)

        Invoked to restore state of this adapter module instance. Note, that this is invoked only in case that the bundle passed to dispatchRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) is valid.

        Parameters:
        savedState - Bundle with saved data populated in the onSaveInstanceState(Bundle). Always valid bundle.

      • onAttachedToAdapter

        protected void onAttachedToAdapter(Adapter adapter)

        Invoked immediately after dispatchAttachToAdapter(com.wit.android.widget.adapter.module.AdapterModule.ModuleAdapter).

        Parameters:
        adapter - The adapter to which was this module right now attached.

      • getAdapter

        protected final Adapter getAdapter()

        Returns the adapter to which is this module attached.

        Returns:
        The attached adapter.

      • notifyAdapter

        protected final void notifyAdapter()

        Notifies the adapter to which is this module attached. This should be fired whenever the data set of this adapter module on which the attached adapter depends, was changed.

        See Also:
        isAdapterNotificationEnabled(), enableAdapterNotification(boolean)
